1 passed resolutions that support admitting the District of Columbia into the Union as a state of the United States
2 of America; and
3 WHEREAS, despite the Constitution establishing that "New States may be admitted by the Congress
4 into this Union", and despite the United States House of Representatives passing the Washington, D.C.
5 Admission Act on June 26, 2020, and again on April 22, 2021, which would declare the state of Washington,
6 Douglass Commonwealth, to be "a State of the United States of America, and declared admitted into the Union
7 on an equal footing with the other States in all respects whatever", Congress has yet to grant full statehood to
8 the approximately 700,000 people of Washington, D.C.
9
10 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
11 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12 (1) That the State of Montana supports admitting Washington, D.C., into the Union as a state of
13 the United States of America.
14 (2) That the State of Montana opposes efforts by Congress and the President of the United States
15 that interfere with local self-government and Home Rule, including federal laws disapproving, amending, and
16 repealing actions of the Council of the District of Columbia and the Mayor of the District of Columbia as well as
17 federal budget riders that control and limit the use of locally raised tax revenue.
18 (3) That the State of Montana calls on Congress and the President of the United States to enact
19 federal legislation granting statehood to the people of Washington, D.C.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State send a copy of this resolution to the
21 President of the United States, the President of the United States Senate, the Speaker of the United States
22 House of Representatives, and each member of the Montana Congressional Delegation.
